.TH "polyglot\-troubleshooting" "7" "" "Runtime Documentation" "Polyglot Devcontainers"
.SH NAME
polyglot\-troubleshooting \- common failures in the container workflow
.SH PURPOSE
This page captures common failure patterns and the preferred recovery
path.
.SH WHEN TO USE
Read this page when the validated starter workflow is blocked.
.SH COMMON FAILURES
.SS \f[CR]task ci\f[R] fails unexpectedly
Recommended response:
.IP \(bu 2
identify the failing stage: init, lint, test, or scan
.IP \(bu 2
inspect the related artifacts under \f[CR].artifacts/scans/\f[R]
.IP \(bu 2
fix the real contract failure before widening the scope
.SS \f[CR]task\f[R] says there is no Taskfile in a published starter image
Recommended response:
.IP \(bu 2
confirm the image is a published starter image and the workspace is
mounted
.IP \(bu 2
if the workspace is empty, run \f[CR]task init\f[R]
.IP \(bu 2
use \f[CR]man polyglot\f[R] and \f[CR]man polyglot\-starters\f[R] before
inventing a custom bootstrap path
.SS \f[CR]task init\f[R] installs many Python or Node packages
Recommended response:
.IP \(bu 2
treat this as expected starter bootstrap behavior
.IP \(bu 2
distinguish between image\-level tooling and project\-local dependencies
.IP \(bu 2
let \f[CR]task init\f[R] finish before evaluating the starter workspace
.SS \f[CR]task scan\f[R] reports Git repository discovery errors in a fresh workspace
Recommended response:
.IP \(bu 2
use a starter image version that falls back cleanly outside Git
repositories
.IP \(bu 2
initialize Git later if your project needs it
.IP \(bu 2
treat Git as optional for starter bootstrap, not a prerequisite
.SS dependency report output looks incomplete
Recommended response:
.IP \(bu 2
inspect \f[CR]dependency\-inventory.json\f[R]
.IP \(bu 2
inspect \f[CR]dependency\-plan.json\f[R]
.IP \(bu 2
confirm the path supports \f[CR]deps:report\f[R]
.SS the host run behaves differently from the container
Recommended response:
.IP \(bu 2
treat the container as the source of truth
.IP \(bu 2
rerun inside the container before drawing conclusions
.SS a starter is too experimental for the job
Recommended response:
.IP \(bu 2
move back to the relevant starter template
.IP \(bu 2
use proving fixtures only when you need the extra maintenance workflow
.SS \f[CR]man polyglot\f[R] is missing in a starter image
Recommended response:
.IP \(bu 2
use a starter image release that ships runtime docs in the image
.IP \(bu 2
if you are validating the repository workspace itself, rebuild the docs
with \f[CR]python scripts/build_runtime_docs.py\f[R]
.IP \(bu 2
treat missing runtime docs in a published starter image as a repository
bug
.SH GUIDANCE
.IP \(bu 2
prefer narrowing the problem before expanding the toolchain
.IP \(bu 2
keep the validated task contract as the anchor
.IP \(bu 2
use local runtime docs first, then deeper repository docs if needed
